## STEP 2 — VM1 Setup (Jenkins + Maven + Ansible)

Connect to VM1 via PuTTY then run:

```bash
sudo su -
nano setup.sh
```

Paste this script:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e

echo "=== Update System ==="
dnf update -y

echo "=== Install Java 21 ==="
dnf install java-21-amazon-corretto -y
java -version

echo "=== Add Jenkins Repo ==="
wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

echo "=== Install Jenkins ==="
dnf install jenkins -y

echo "=== Set JAVA_HOME for Jenkins ==="
mkdir -p /etc/systemd/system/jenkins.service.d
cat > /etc/systemd/system/jenkins.service.d/override.conf << EOF
[Service]
Environment="JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-amazon-corretto.x86_64"
EOF

echo "=== Start Jenkins ==="
systemctl daemon-reload
systemctl start jenkins
systemctl enable jenkins

echo "=== Install Git, Maven, Ansible ==="
dnf install git maven ansible -y

echo "=== Jenkins Unlock Password ==="
cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```

Run it:

```bash
chmod +x setup.sh
bash setup.sh
```

